oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Firefighters putting out a fire at the G. N. Mize and Son Lumber Company on High Street
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The lumber yard caught fire from sparks made by a switching train. It burned 7 boxcar loads of lumber, the lumber yard, and Southern Coffin and Casket Company.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Fires; Fire fighters; Firefighting equipment; Buildings; Lumber industry
